<plot>A contemplative silent film about a terminal cancer diagnosed chess enthusiast, reflecting on life and death, while reenacting one of the classic matches between the legendary grandmasters; Alexander Alekhine and Max Euwe in the World Chess Championship 1937. A film about genius and skill, tragedy and comedy, black and white, life and death and the noble art of chess.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?460790</url></doc>
